 {"id":"bd-7n4r","title":"unistd: execute unistd_ops.json fixture family through harness matrix","description":"Concrete gap: crates/frankenlibc-harness/tests/unistd_ops_conformance_test.rs currently stops at schema/coverage assertions and never executes tests/conformance/fixtures/unistd_ops.json. Add harness-matrix execution for the unistd fixture family, assert expected_output/host parity in strict+hardened modes where applicable, and fix any syscall-wrapper mismatches surfaced by the new executable coverage.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"AmberSignal","created_at":"2026-04-21T03:54:37.810550233Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T11:25:40.338024453Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T11:25:40.335868573Z","close_reason":"Executed unistd_ops.json through the harness conformance matrix, preserving expected_output and host-parity assertions for stable cases and matching the existing dynamic-fd skip contract; verified locally and via rch.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"bd-7rxtm","title":"fuzz: add coverage-guided harness for strftime format-string parser","description":"strftime is a format-string parser (~50 specifiers + flags + length modifiers + locale-sensitive output) with no current fuzz coverage. Add crates/frankenlibc-fuzz/fuzz_targets/fuzz_strftime.rs that exercises frankenlibc_core::time::format_strftime with arbitrary format bytes + arbitrary BrokenDownTime fields and a fixed output buffer. Differential check vs libc::strftime is hard (locale state matters); start with crash-detector + invariant checks: no panic, no buffer overrun (return value <= maxsize), determinism on repeated calls. Per /testing-fuzzing skill (Archetype 1).","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:06:47.199509348Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:06:54.205722087Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-7rxtm","title":"fuzz: add coverage-guided harness for strftime format-string parser","description":"strftime is a format-string parser (~50 specifiers + flags + length modifiers + locale-sensitive output) with no current fuzz coverage. Add crates/frankenlibc-fuzz/fuzz_targets/fuzz_strftime.rs that exercises frankenlibc_core::time::format_strftime with arbitrary format bytes + arbitrary BrokenDownTime fields and a fixed output buffer. Differential check vs libc::strftime is hard (locale state matters); start with crash-detector + invariant checks: no panic, no buffer overrun (return value <= maxsize), determinism on repeated calls. Per /testing-fuzzing skill (Archetype 1).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:06:47.199509348Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T08:17:01.459756827Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T08:17:01.457528289Z","close_reason":"fuzz_strftime committed + two i32 overflow panics found and fixed: iso_week (bd-7rxtm used to pass tm_yday/tm_wday through i32 arithmetic) and %U/%W week-number formatting. All three sites widened to i64. Regression test format_strftime_does_not_overflow_on_extreme_tm_fields pins i32::MIN/MAX/edge inputs. 22K-exec fuzz pass clean after fixes. Committed ae472b5.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
